I guess the problem lies in the super class.
I see that the super class is invoking a deprecated method, and we should be invoking appendWidgetContextName according to the Javadoc.

So, my recommendation would be to remove the context attribute in ViewCasePage and the following method to be:
	@Override
	public String createContextName(com.fineos.common.portalinfrastructure.Parameters parameters, BusinessEntity mainObject) {
		CaseContextResolver caseContextResolver = new DefaultCaseContextResolver();
		return caseContextResolver.resolveContext((OCCase)mainObject);
    }
From my reading of it, the assignment to context attribute is not necessary in ViewCasePage, as it will be set in the super class&#39;s setContextNameOnPage method (its only reference in the workspace - that I could find). The SuperClass&#39; setContextNameOnPage should be modified to use appendWidgetContextName(resolvedContext).

Any future requirement to store the value returned from this method can be simply a setter or assignment.
